 в”Ӯ                                           в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ        в”Ӯ              Header: x-agentcube-session-id                    в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ        в”Ӯ              Body: JSON payload                                в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ        в”Ӯ                                           в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ        в–ј                                           в–ј              в–ј       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ Validate в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ GET      в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ Header   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ Return   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ Close    в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ router_  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ /v1/namesв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ + JSON   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ JSON     в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ requests в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ url      в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ paces/...в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ body     в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ data     в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ .Session в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                        /invocations/                                       в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **CodeInterpreterClient** | High-level Code Interpreter interface | Config params, commands, code | Execution results, file handles |\n| **AgentRuntimeClient** | High-level Agent Runtime interface | Agent name, payload | Invocation response |\n| **ControlPlaneClient** | Workload Manager API client | Session parameters | Session ID |\n| **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient** | Router API for Code Interpreter | Commands, files | Results, file data |\n| **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** | Router API for Agent Runtime | Session ID, payload | HTTP response |\n| **create_session** | HTTP session factory | Pool settings | Configured Session |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ __init__.py                      # Public exports (~30 lines)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ code_interpreter.py              # CodeInterpreterClient (~320 lines)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ agent_runtime.py                 # AgentRuntimeClient (~130 lines)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ exceptions.py                    # Exception classes (~60 lines)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ clients/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ __init__.py                  # Re-exports (~15 lines)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ control_plane.py             # ControlPlaneClient (~155 lines)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ code_interpreter_data_plane.py   # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (~265 lines)\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ agent_runtime_data_plane.py      # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (~130 lines)\nв””в”Җв”Җ utils/\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ __init__.py                  # Module marker\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ http.py                      # create_session, read_token_from_file (~65 lines)\n    в””в”Җв”Җ log.py                       # get_logger (~30 lines)\n\npyproject.toml                       # Package configuration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Domain Types\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter session management and execution.\n\n    Attributes:\n        name: Session name (default: \"my-interpreter\").\n        namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\").\n        ttl: Session TTL in seconds (default: 3600).\n        verbose: Enable verbose logging.\n        logger: Logger instance.\n        cp_client: Control plane client.\n        router_url: Router URL.\n        session_id: Session ID (created or provided).\n        dp_client: Data plane client.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation.\n\n    Attributes:\n        agent_name: Name of the agent to invoke.\n        namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\").\n        timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120).\n        connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0).\n        logger: Logger instance.\n        router_url: Router URL.\n        session_id: Session ID (bootstrapped or provided).\n        dp_client: Data plane client.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n#### ControlPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Client for Workload Manager control plane API.\n\n    Attributes:\n        base_url: The Workload Manager base URL.\n        timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n        connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n        session: The HTTP session with connection pooling.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Client for Code Interpreter data plane operations.\n\n    Attributes:\n        session_id: The session ID for header injection.\n        base_url: The data plane base URL.\n        timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n        connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n        session: The HTTP session with connection pooling.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        base_url: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n\n    Attributes:\n        base_url: The data plane base URL.\n        timeout: Read timeout in seconds.\n        connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds.\n        session: The HTTP session with connection pooling.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n```\n\n### Request/Response Types\n\n#### Code Interpreter Session Creation Request\n\n```python\n# POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n{\n    \"name\": str,          # Session name\n    \"namespace\": str,     # Kubernetes namespace\n    \"ttl\": int,           # TTL in seconds\n    \"metadata\": dict,     # Optional metadata\n}\n\n# Response\n{\n    \"sessionId\": str,     # Unique session identifier\n}\n```\n\n#### Code Interpreter Execute Request\n\n```python\n# POST api/execute\n{\n    \"command\": List[str],     # Command as list of strings\n    \"timeout\": str,           # Timeout string (e.g., \"60s\")\n}\n\n# Response\n{\n    \"stdout\": str,\n    \"stderr\": str,\n    \"exit_code\": int,\n}\n```\n\n#### Code Interpreter Files Request\n\n```python\n# POST api/files (JSON)\n{\n    \"path\": str,          # Remote file path\n    \"content\": str,       # Base64-encoded content\n    \"mode\": str,          # File permissions (e.g., \"0644\")\n}\n\n# POST api/files (Multipart)\n# Form data:\n#   - file: binary content\n#   - path: remote path\n#   - mode: permissions\n\n# GET api/files/{clean_path}\n# Returns: File content as binary\n\n# GET api/files?path={path}\n# Returns: List[Dict[str, Any]] file listings\n```\n\n#### Agent Runtime Invoke Request\n\n```python\n# GET {base_url}\n# Response headers:\n#   x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>\n\n# POST {base_url}\n# Headers:\n#   x-agentcube-session-id: <session_id>\n#   Content-Type: application/json\n# Body: Dict[str, Any] (payload)\n# Response: JSON data\n```\n\n### Internal Types\n\n#### HTTP Session Configuration\n\n```python\nfrom requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\n\nclass SessionConfig:\n    \"\"\"Configuration for HTTP session.\"\"\"\n    pool_connections: int = 10\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10\n    timeout: int = 120\n    connect_timeout: float = 5.0\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n```python\n# Default configuration values\nDEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\nDEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0\nDEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS = 10\nDEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE = 10\nDEFAULT_TTL = 3600\nDEFAULT_NAMESPACE = \"default\"\n\n# Session header name\nSESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n# Service account token path\nSERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN_PATH = \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n\n# Environment variable names\nENV_ROUTER_URL = \"ROUTER_URL\"\nENV_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL = \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### CodeInterpreterClient Interface\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClientInterface(Protocol):\n    \"\"\"Interface for CodeInterpreterClient.\n\n    Provides lifecycle management for Code Interpreter sessions and\n    operations for executing commands and managing files.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def execute_command(\n        self,\n        command: List[str],\n        timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Execute a command in the Code Interpreter.\n\n        Returns:\n            Dictionary with stdout, stderr, and exit_code.\n\n        Raises:\n            CommandExecutionError: If command returns non-zero exit code.\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def run_code(\n        self,\n        code: str,\n        language: str = \"python\",\n        timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Execute code in the Code Interpreter.\n\n        For Python: writes timestamped .py file and executes with python3.\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def write_file(self, path: str, content: str, mode: str = \"0644\") -> None:\n        \"\"\"Write a file to the Code Interpreter workspace.\"\"\"\n\n    def upload_file(\n        self,\n        path: str,\n        content: Union[str, bytes, os.PathLike],\n        mode: str = \"0644\",\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Upload a file via multipart/form-data.\"\"\"\n\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str) -> bytes:\n        \"\"\"Download a file from the Code Interpreter workspace.\"\"\"\n\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \"/\") -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n        \"\"\"List files in the Code Interpreter workspace.\"\"\"\n\n    def stop(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Stop the client and clean up resources.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient Interface\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClientInterface(Protocol):\n    \"\"\"Interface for AgentRuntimeClient.\n\n    Provides interface for invoking Agent Runtime workloads through\n    the Router API with session management.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Invoke the Agent Runtime with a payload.\n\n        Args:\n            payload: JSON payload to send to the agent.\n            timeout: Optional timeout override in seconds.\n\n        Returns:\n            Response data as dictionary.\n\n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If session_id is not initialized.\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the client and release resources.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### ControlPlaneClient Interface\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClientInterface(Protocol):\n    \"\"\"Interface for ControlPlaneClient.\n\n    Manages session lifecycle through the Workload Manager API.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def create_session(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Create a new Code Interpreter session.\n\n        Returns:\n            The session ID string.\n\n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If response missing sessionId.\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Delete a Code Interpreter session.\n\n        Returns:\n            True if deletion succeeded or session not found (404).\n            False if deletion failed.\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Data Plane Clients Interface\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClientInterface(Protocol):\n    \"\"\"Data plane client for Code Interpreter operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def execute_command(\n        self,\n        command: List[str],\n        timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def write_file(\n        self,\n        path: str,\n        content: Union[str, bytes],\n        mode: str = \"0644\",\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n    def upload_file(\n        self,\n        path: str,\n        content: Union[str, bytes, os.PathLike],\n        mode: str = \"0644\",\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str) -> bytes: ...\n\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \"/\") -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n\n\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClientInterface(Protocol):\n    \"\"\"Data plane client for Agent Runtime operations.\"\"\"\n\n    SESSION_HEADER: str = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Bootstrap session ID from invocation endpoint.\n\n        Returns:\n            Session ID from response header.\n\n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If session header missing.\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"Invoke Agent Runtime with payload.\n\n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If session_id is falsy.\n        \"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### HTTP Utilities\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create an HTTP session with connection pooling.\n\n    Mounts HTTPAdapter for http:// and https://.\n    \"\"\"\n\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Read authentication token from file.\n\n    Returns:\n        Token string stripped, or \"\" on FileNotFoundError.\n    \"\"\"\n\ndef get_service_account_token() -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"Read Kubernetes service account token.\n\n    Reads from /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories and Codes\n\n| Error | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ValueError` | Missing required URL or session ID | No | Fail fast with clear message |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command non-zero exit | No | Raise with exit_code, stderr |\n| `requests.RequestException` | HTTP request failure | Varies | Re-raise for caller handling |\n| `SessionError` | Session management failure | Context | Available for extension |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Data plane operation failure | Context | Available for extension |\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when remote command returns non-zero exit code.\n\n    Attributes:\n        exit_code: The exit code returned.\n        stderr: Standard error output.\n        command: The executed command.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        exit_code: int,\n        stderr: str,\n        command: Optional[str] = None,\n    ):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        message = f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n        if command:\n            message = f\"Command '{command}' failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n        super().__init__(message)\n\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\n\n    Defined for extension; core clients primarily use ValueError.\n    \"\"\"\n    pass\n\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\n\n    Defined for extension; core clients use requests exceptions.\n    \"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n#### Router URL Validation\n\n```python\ndef __init__(self, ..., router_url: Optional[str] = None, ...):\n    self.router_url = router_url or os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n    if not self.router_url:\n        raise ValueError(\n            \"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\"\n        )\n```\n\n#### Session ID Validation\n\n```python\ndef invoke(self, session_id: str, ...):\n    if not session_id:\n        raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")\n    # ... proceed with invocation\n```\n\n#### Command Execution Error\n\n```python\ndef execute_command(self, command: List[str], ...):\n    response = self._request(\"POST\", \"api/execute\", ...)\n    data = response.json()\n    exit_code = data.get(\"exit_code\", 0)\n\n    if exit_code != 0:\n        raise CommandExecutionError(\n            exit_code=exit_code,\n            stderr=data.get(\"stderr\", \"\"),\n            command=\" \".join(command),\n        )\n    return data\n```\n\n#### Bootstrap Session Error\n\n```python\ndef bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n    response = self.session.get(self.base_url, ...)\n    response.raise_for_status()\n\n    session_id = response.headers.get(self.SESSION_HEADER)\n    if not session_id:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Missing required response header: {self.SESSION_HEADER}\")\n    return session_id\n```\n\n#### Cleanup on Failure\n\n```python\ndef _create_and_init_session(self) -> None:\n    try:\n        self.session_id = self.cp_client.create_session(...)\n        self._init_data_plane()\n    except Exception:\n        # Clean up session if data plane init failed\n        if self.session_id and self._session_created_by_client:\n            self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n            self.session_id = None\n        raise\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### test_code_interpreter_client.py\n\n```python\ndef test_code_interpreter_client_requires_router_url():\n    \"\"\"Router URL must be provided or set in environment.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Router URL must be provided\"):\n        CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=None)\n    # Ensure ROUTER_URL env is not set\n    old_env = os.environ.pop(\"ROUTER_URL\", None)\n    try:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Router URL must be provided\"):\n            CodeInterpreterClient()\n    finally:\n        if old_env:\n            os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"] = old_env\n\n\ndef test_code_interpreter_client_reuses_session_id(mock_cp_client, mock_dp_client):\n    \"\"\"Client reuses provided session_id without creating new session.\"\"\"\n    with patch.object(\n        agentcube.code_interpreter, \"ControlPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_cp_client\n    ):\n        with patch.object(\n            agentcube.code_interpreter,\n            \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n            return_value=mock_dp_client,\n        ):\n            client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n                router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n                session_id=\"existing-session-123\",\n            )\n            assert client.session_id == \"existing-session-123\"\n            mock_cp_client.create_session.assert_not_called()\n\n\ndef test_code_interpreter_client_cleanup_on_dp_init_failure(mock_cp_client):\n    \"\"\"Session is deleted if data plane init fails after creation.\"\"\"\n    mock_cp_client.create_session.return_value = \"new-session-456\"\n\n    with patch.object(\n        agentcube.code_interpreter, \"ControlPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_cp_client\n    ):\n        with patch.object(\n            agentcube.code_interpreter,\n            \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n            side_effect=Exception(\"Connection failed\"),\n        ):\n            with pytest.raises(Exception, match=\"Connection failed\"):\n                CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n\n            # Session should be cleaned up\n            mock_cp_client.delete_session.assert_called_once_with(\"new-session-456\")\n\n\ndef test_context_manager_calls_stop(mock_client):\n    \"\"\"Context manager calls stop() on exit.\"\"\"\n    with mock_client as client:\n        pass\n    mock_client.stop.assert_called_once()\n\n\ndef test_execute_command_raises_on_non_zero_exit(mock_dp_client):\n    \"\"\"CommandExecutionError raised when exit_code != 0.\"\"\"\n    mock_dp_client.execute_command.return_value = {\n        \"stdout\": \"\",\n        \"stderr\": \"error message\",\n        \"exit_code\": 1,\n    }\n    # Test logic...\n```\n\n#### test_agent_runtime_client.py\n\n```python\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_requires_router_url():\n    \"\"\"Router URL must be provided or set in environment.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Router URL must be provided\"):\n        AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=None)\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_bootstrap_session_id(mock_dp_client):\n    \"\"\"Client bootstraps session_id when not provided.\"\"\"\n    mock_dp_client.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"bootstrapped-session\"\n\n    with patch.object(\n        agentcube.agent_runtime, \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_dp_client\n    ):\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n        )\n        assert client.session_id == \"bootstrapped-session\"\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_client_uses_provided_session_id(mock_dp_client):\n    \"\"\"Client uses provided session_id without bootstrapping.\"\"\"\n    mock_dp_client.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"bootstrapped-session\"\n\n    with patch.object(\n        agentcube.agent_runtime, \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\", return_value=mock_dp_client\n    ):\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=\"provided-session\",\n        )\n        assert client.session_id == \"provided-session\"\n        mock_dp_client.bootstrap_session_id.assert_not_called()\n\n\ndef test_invoke_raises_without_session(mock_client):\n    \"\"\"ValueError raised when invoking without session_id.\"\"\"\n    mock_client.session_id = None\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"session_id is not initialized\"):\n        mock_client.invoke({\"key\": \"value\"})\n\n\ndef test_context_manager_calls_close(mock_client):\n    \"\"\"Context manager calls close() on exit.\"\"\"\n    with mock_client as client:\n        pass\n    mock_client.close.assert_called_once()\n```\n\n#### test_control_plane_client.py\n\n```python\ndef test_create_session_returns_session_id(mock_session):\n    \"\"\"create_session returns sessionId from response.\"\"\"\n    mock_response = Mock()\n    mock_response.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\n    mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n\n    client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n    client.session = mock_session\n\n    session_id = client.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\")\n    assert session_id == \"session-123\"\n\n\ndef test_create_session_raises_on_missing_session_id(mock_session):\n    \"\"\"ValueError raised when response missing sessionId.\"\"\"\n    mock_response = Mock()\n    mock_response.json.return_value = {}  # No sessionId\n    mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n\n    client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n    client.session = mock_session\n\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"sessionId\"):\n        client.create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\")\n\n\ndef test_delete_session_returns_true_on_404(mock_session):\n    \"\"\"delete_session returns True on 404 (already deleted).\"\"\"\n    mock_response = Mock()\n    mock_response.status_code = 404\n    mock_session.delete.return_value = mock_response\n\n    client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")\n    client.session = mock_session\n\n    result = client.delete_session(\"session-123\")\n    assert result is True\n```\n\n#### test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n\n```python\ndef test_bootstrap_session_id_from_header(mock_session):\n    \"\"\"bootstrap_session_id extracts session ID from response header.\"\"\"\n    mock_response = Mock()\n    mock_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-123\"}\n    mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n\n    client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n    client.session = mock_session\n\n    session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n    assert session_id == \"session-123\"\n\n\ndef test_bootstrap_session_id_raises_on_missing_header(mock_session):\n    \"\"\"ValueError raised when session header missing.\"\"\"\n    mock_response = Mock()\n    mock_response.headers = {}  # No session header\n    mock_session.get.return_value = mock_response\n\n    client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n    client.session = mock_session\n\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"x-agentcube-session-id\"):\n        client.bootstrap_session_id()\n\n\ndef test_invoke_sets_session_header(mock_session):\n    \"\"\"invoke sets x-agentcube-session-id header.\"\"\"\n    mock_response = Mock()\n    mock_session.post.return_value = mock_response\n\n    client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n    client.session = mock_session\n\n    client.invoke(\n        session_id=\"session-123\",\n        payload={\"key\": \"value\"},\n    )\n\n    call_kwargs = mock_session.post.call_args[1]\n    headers = call_kwargs.get(\"headers\", {})\n    assert headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\") == \"session-123\"\n\n\ndef test_invoke_raises_on_empty_session_id():\n    \"\"\"ValueError raised when session_id is empty.\"\"\"\n    client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://router:8080/invocations/\")\n\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"session_id\"):\n        client.invoke(session_id=\"\", payload={})\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\ndef test_code_interpreter_end_to_end():\n    \"\"\"Integration test for Code Interpreter flow.\"\"\"\n    if not os.environ.get(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"):\n        pytest.skip(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL not set\")\n\n    router_url = os.environ[\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"]\n    workload_manager_url = os.environ.get(\"TEST_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(\n        router_url=router_url,\n        workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n    ) as client:\n        # Execute command\n        result = client.execute_command([\"echo\", \"hello\"])\n        assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 0\n        assert \"hello\" in result[\"stdout\"]\n\n        # Write and read file\n        client.write_file(\"/workspace/test.txt\", \"test content\")\n        content = client.download_file(\"/workspace/test.txt\")\n        assert content.decode() == \"test content\"\n\n        # List files\n        files = client.list_files(\"/workspace\")\n        assert any(f[\"name\"] == \"test.txt\" for f in files)\n\n\ndef test_agent_runtime_end_to_end():\n    \"\"\"Integration test for Agent Runtime flow.\"\"\"\n    if not os.environ.get(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"):\n        pytest.skip(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL not set\")\n\n    router_url = os.environ[\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"]\n    agent_name = os.environ.get(\"TEST_AGENT_NAME\", \"test-agent\")\n\n    with AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=agent_name,\n        router_url=router_url,\n    ) as client:\n        response = client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"})\n        assert \"output\" in response\n```\n\n### Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all SDK tests\npytest tests/ -v\n\n# Run specific test modules\npytest tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py -v\npytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py -v\npytest tests/test_control_plane.py -v\n\n# Run with coverage\npytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=html\n\n# Run integration tests\npytest tests/ -m integration --env-file=.env.test\n```\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication\n\n- **Service Account Token**: Automatically read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n- **Bearer Token**: Set as `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on control plane requests\n- **Router JWT**: Handled by Router; SDK does not set Authorization on data plane requests\n\n### Session Header\n\n- **Session ID**: Passed via `x-agentcube-session-id` header on all data plane requests\n- **Lowercase Header**: Consistent lowercase header name across all clients\n\n### URL Validation\n\n```python\n# Router URL is required\nif not self.router_url:\n    raise ValueError(\"Router URL must be provided...\")\n\n# Workload Manager URL is required for control plane operations\nif not self.base_url:\n    raise ValueError(\"Workload Manager URL must be provided...\")\n```\n\n### Timeout Safety\n\n```python\n# Read timeout buffer for command execution\n# Avoids ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124\nread_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0\n```\n\n---\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Connection Pooling\n\n| Setting | Default | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| pool_connections | 10 | Number of connection pools to cache |\n| pool_maxsize | 10 | Maximum connections to save per pool |\n| timeout | 120s | Default read timeout |\n| connect_timeout | 5.0s | Connection establishment timeout |\n\n### Timeout Behavior\n\n| Operation | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout |\n|-----------|-----------------|--------------|\n| Control plane | 5.0s | 120s |\n| Data plane execute | 5.0s | timeout + 2.0s |\n| Data plane invoke | 5.0s | 120s (configurable) |\n| Bootstrap session | 5.0s | 120s |\n\n### Resource Management\n\n- **Context Managers**: All clients support `with` statement for automatic cleanup\n- **Session Reuse**: Single HTTP session per client with connection pooling\n- **Explicit Close**: `close()` method for resource cleanup outside context managers\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### With Workload Manager (Control Plane)\n\n```python\n# Create session\nPOST {workload_manager_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n# Body: {\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}\n# Response: {\"sessionId\"}\n\n# Delete session\nDELETE {workload_manager_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\n```\n\n### With Router (Data Plane - Code Interpreter)\n\n```python\n# Base URL construction\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{name}/invocations/\"\nbase_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n\n# Execute command\nPOST {base_url}/api/execute\n# Body: {\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}\n\n# Write file\nPOST {base_url}/api/files\n# Body: {\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\"}\n\n# Upload file\nPOST {base_url}/api/files (multipart)\n# Form: files={'file': ...}, data={'path', 'mode'}\n\n# Download file\nGET {base_url}/api/files/{clean_path}\n# Response: File content (stream=True)\n\n# List files\nGET {base_url}/api/files?path={path}\n# Response: List of file info\n```\n\n### With Router (Data Plane - Agent Runtime)\n\n```python\n# Base URL construction\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nbase_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n\n# Bootstrap session\nGET {base_url}\n# Response header: x-agentcube-session-id\n\n# Invoke\nPOST {base_url}\n# Headers: x-agentcube-session-id, Content-Type: application/json\n# Body: JSON payload\n# Response: JSON data\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```toml\n# pyproject.toml\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube-cli\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.9\"\n\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests>=2.31.0\",\n    # ... other dependencies\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    # ...\n]\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose | Version |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `requests` | HTTP client with session pooling | >=2.31.0 |\n| `pytest` | Testing framework | >=7.4.0 (dev) |\n| `pytest-cov` | Coverage reporting | >=4.1.0 (dev) |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [AgentCube Python SDK Specification](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md) вҖ” Detailed SDK specification\n- [Code Interpreter Client](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py) вҖ” CodeInterpreterClient implementation\n- [Agent Runtime Client](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py) вҖ” AgentRuntimeClient implementation\n- [Control Plane Client](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py) вҖ” ControlPlaneClient implementation\n- [Code Interpreter Data Plane](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py) вҖ” CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient implementation\n- [Agent Runtime Data Plane](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py) вҖ” AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implementation\n- [Exceptions](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/exceptions.py) вҖ” Exception hierarchy\n- [HTTP Utilities](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/utils/http.py) вҖ” HTTP session factory\n\n---\n\n*AR-028 вҖ” Module: sdk-python вҖ” Language: Python вҖ” Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/__init__.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/exceptions.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bai